    I agree with what Sachin said, with one minor change. There is another
member function in Assert called fail() which you can use:

    public void testXXX( ) throws Exception
    {
      try
      {
        doMyStuffThatMightThrow( );
        fail( &quot;Didn&#39;t get my expected exception&quot; );
      }
      catch( MyExpectedException e )
      {
      }
    }

    Same thing as the previous poster, just replace his assert( false ) with
fail().

